<subSubSection id="72DD2B11EC2768FF4007B91292E70DB4" pageId="14" pageNumber="229" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="67E06D4CF27C12ABB53DE48F4677DAD2" pageId="14" pageNumber="229">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="473FD219536FAA3C83DA624AB458B98F" pageId="14" pageNumber="229">
Mystax whitish. Katatergal setae whitish. Anatergite with white setae. Scutellum disc with minute yellow-white setae. Mesonotal macrosetae yellow-white. Wings: Discal cell lacking microtrichia. Legs: Femora black and yellow-brown. ♀ with abdominal segments 1-6 pruinose. ♂ terminalia as in 
<figureCitation id="68065449EFE7CD04775D5E3938F6D6AA" captionStart="Figures 1–4" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 4. Lateral views of Astochia male terminalia as illustrated by Londt (1982): 1 A. africana 2 A. armata 3 A. sodalis 4 A. strachani." figureDoi="10.3897/AfrInvertebr.60.38432.figures1-4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/346335" pageId="14" pageNumber="229" tableDoi="10.3897/AfrInvertebr.60.38432.figures1-4">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
. The species was fully redescribed by 
<bibRefCitation id="5B751A5D248BF5510EAFA8E38CD79FFB" author="Londt, JGH" journalOrPublisher="Annals of the Natal Museum" pageId="19" pageNumber="234" pagination="241 - 251" refId="B11" refString="Londt, JGH, 1982. Afrotropical Asilidae (Diptera) 7. The genus Astochia Becker, 1913 (Asilinae: Asilini). Annals of the Natal Museum 25: 241 - 251" title="Afrotropical Asilidae (Diptera) 7. The genus Astochia Becker, 1913 (Asilinae: Asilini)." volume="25" year="1982">Londt (1982)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
